<hint name="helpSection"><title>Worked Example</title>
    <p>We first need to notice that this problem has a greatest common factor. Then, we can proceed to factoring the remaining quadratic. Here is a similar worked example:</p>
      <md>
        <mrow>2x^2 - 26x + 84 \amp= 2(x^2 - 13x + 42)\;\;\text{factor out GCF = 2}</mrow>
        <mrow>\amp= 2(x - 6)(x - 7)</mrow>
      </md> 
<p><em>How to check</em>: Always FOIL it out to see if it matches your original expression.</p>
