<!--*********************************************
            Solution
**********************************************-->
<solution>
<p>First, check to see what the greatest common factor of all three terms is. In this case, the <m>GCF = $m</m>.</p>
<p>Factoring out the <m>GCF</m>, consider the remaining trinomial: 
  <me><math name="GCF_factoredOut" simplify>x^2-($b+$a)x+$a$b</math>.</me></p>
  
<p>Now we need to find two factors of <math simplify>$a$b</math> that sum to <math simplify>-($b+$a)</math>. The two factors are <m>-$a</m> and <m>-$b</m>.</p>
<p>We can now factor the trinomial as
  <me>$factoredExpr{simplify}.</me> 
</p>

</solution>
</problem>
